Package: nextstat
Type: Package
Title: High-Performance Statistical Inference via Rust
Version: 0.9.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("NextStat", "Contributors", email = "dev@nextstat.io", role = c("aut", "cre"))
  )
Description: R interface to the NextStat statistical inference engine
    written in Rust. Provides population PK/PD modeling (FOCE/FOCEI, SAEM),
    pharmacodynamic models (Emax, sigmoid Emax, indirect response Types I-IV),
    adaptive ODE solvers for stiff PK/PD systems, stepwise covariate modeling
    (SCM), VPC/GOF diagnostics, HistFactory maximum-likelihood fitting,
    asymptotic CLs hypothesis testing, upper limits (Brazil bands),
    generalized linear models (logistic, Poisson, negative binomial),
    Kalman filter/smoother, GARCH(1,1), and stochastic volatility models.
    All computations are performed in compiled Rust code via 'extendr'.
License: AGPL-3 | file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
